President George W. Bush faced hostility during his farewell visit to Iraq when a journalist threw shoes at him, symbolizing the mixed feelings towards the outgoing leader.
Despite the incident, Bush defended the Iraq war, emphasizing the necessity and progress made.
The shoe-throwing journalist, Muntadar al-Zeidi, expressed the resentment felt by many Iraqis towards Bush's policies.
The security agreement signed between the US and Iraq marked a new era in the conflict that has had lasting impacts on both nations.
Bush's visit, shrouded in secrecy, highlighted the complexities and consequences of his presidency.
